# Project Documentation

# Sales & Financial Analysis Dashboard

## Project Overview

This project focuses on analyzing company sales, revenue, expenses, and profitability to evaluate overall business performance and operational efficiency. The dashboard was developed using Microsoft Excel with Pivot Tables, Pivot Charts, and Power Query for data transformation and interactive reporting.

The primary objective of this project is to help business stakeholders monitor financial health, identify high-performing regions and products, and understand the relationship between sales growth and profitability.

---

# Business Problem

Businesses often generate strong sales revenue but struggle to maintain healthy profit margins due to increasing operational costs, excessive discounts, or inefficient financial management.

The company required an analytical dashboard to

- Monitor overall sales and financial performance
- Identify high-performing products and regions
- Analyze profitability trends
- Evaluate the impact of discounts on profit margins
- Track operational expenses and business efficiency

---

# Project Objectives

- Analyze company-wide sales and financial performance
- Track revenue, expenses, and profit trends
- Identify profitable and low-performing business segments
- Measure financial efficiency using KPIs
- Provide actionable business insights for decision-making

---

# Dataset Information

The dataset contains transactional financial and sales-related data including

- Sales
- Profit
- Discounts
- Manufacturing Cost
- Revenue
- Product Segments
- Countries
- Units Sold
- Monthly Sales Trends

The dataset was cleaned and transformed before dashboard development.

---

# Data Cleaning & Preparation

Data preparation was performed using Power Query and Excel functions.

Key cleaning steps included

- Removing unnecessary columns
- Handling blank values
- Correcting data types
- Converting currency fields into numerical format
- Creating calculated KPIs and percentage metrics
- Creating Month Sort columns for proper chronological analysis

